ds of their bodies. Through diverse essays, personal accounts, and poems, contributors portray everyday lives in which meaning comes from movement and from the companions they move with in a variety of activities from running, walking, swimming, and skiing to boxing, Morris dancing, and yoga, among others. A unique, positive, and largely unremarked view of exercise and its place in women's lives, this book will resonate with and inspire many readers.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aDance for womenxPsychological aspects. 0aExercise for womenxPsychological aspects. 0aFeminism. 4aCultural Studies : Cultural Studies. 4aGender and Sexuality : Women's Studies. 4aGeneral Interest : Biography. 4aHealth and Medicine : Health Care. 4aSociology : Sports and Society. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Women's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBloom, Lynn Z., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBoynton, Victoria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrady, Jacqueline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapo, Beth Widmaier, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCorrie-Cozart, Virginia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCoulter, Myrl, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aD’Alo, Grace, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHouser, Catherine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJensen, Marlene, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalin, Jo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalin, Jo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMamary, Anne, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNewhall